    • FAQs

      Questions you may have, answered with
      • What factors affect the grade of a Walking Liberty half dollar?
        The grade of a Walking Liberty half dollar is influenced by its condition, including the sharpness of its details, the presence of any wear or damage, and its luster. Coins with minimal wear and strong, clear details typically receive higher grades. Collectors should look for coins with well-defined features, especially in high-relief areas like Liberty's hand and the eagle's feathers.
        How'd we do?
        Leave feedback about your eBay search experience - opens in new window or tabLeave feedback about your eBay search experience - opens in new window or tab
      • How does the mint mark location influence the coin's rarity?
        Walking Liberty half dollars were minted at Philadelphia, Denver, and San Francisco. Coins without a mint mark are from Philadelphia. Denver (D) and San Francisco (S) mint marks are found on the reverse, below the eagle. Coins from San Francisco are often more sought after due to lower mintage numbers in certain years, potentially increasing their collectibility.
        How'd we do?
        Leave feedback about your eBay search experience - opens in new window or tabLeave feedback about your eBay search experience - opens in new window or tab
      • What are key dates for Walking Liberty half dollars?
        Key dates for Walking Liberty half dollars that are highly sought after by collectors include 1916 and 1921, especially those minted in Denver and San Francisco. The 1938-D is also notable for its lower mintage. Collectors often seek these specific years for their rarity and potential historical value.
